# Semgrep ignore file.
#
# Semgrep ships a default .semgrepignore that excludes broad swaths of
# common test/build directories (including `tests/`, `node_modules/`,
# `target/`, etc.). When this project file is present, Semgrep uses it
# *instead* of the default — so we re-list the exclusions we still
# want, and explicitly *don't* list `tests/fixtures/sast/` (the SAST
# test inputs that the rules in `.semgrep/` are meant to scan).
#
# Patterns follow `.gitignore` syntax.

# Build outputs.
target/
build/
out/
dist/

# Vendored / generated.
node_modules/
.cargo/
.gradle/

# IDE and OS noise.
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# Secret-scan fixtures (covered by gitleaks + trufflehog, not Semgrep;
# Semgrep would rediscover the shaped-but-fake AWS key and add noise to
# the SAST surface).
tests/fixtures/secrets/

# Corpus inputs for benchmarks/integration tests — large, generated,
# and not meaningful targets for source-pattern matching.
test-corpus/
corpus/
crates/barista-bench/corpus/

# Do NOT add `tests/` here — the SAST fixtures at
# `tests/fixtures/sast/` are required Semgrep inputs.
